OL,5, Wages are rising at their fastest rate 
OL,6, in more than 20 years, but still lag   
OL,7, well behind the soaring cost of living.
OL,9,FPay rose at 5.7% in the year to        
OL,10,FSeptember, the fastest growth since    
OL,11,F2000 excluding the pandemic, when      
OL,12,Fpeople got big rises returning to work 
OL,13,Ffrom furlough.                         
OL,15,FHowever when adjusted for rising       
OL,16,Fprices, wages fell by 2.7%.            
OL,18,FThe cost of living is currently rising 
OL,19,Fat its fastest rate in almost 40 years,
OL,20,Fin part due to the war Ukraine.        
